  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Intervention and Exit Strategy to Limit and Prevent Cholera, Kivus</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project remains both the continuity of the four previous phases but stands out by reinforcing the exit strategy marked by the consolidation of the involvement and coordination of the mechanisms of responses by local actors and the development of a market Local chlorinated product to strengthen cholera prevention. ACF will operate in six health zones, including two health zones (Kirotshe in North Kivu and Minova in South Kivu). This proposal is based on the interim report submitted to ECHO in November 2015 to provide baseline data and recent information. However, a final KAP survey will take place in March 2016 and the final results from this activity will allow the basic data and information of this project to be adjusted.</narrative>
  </description>
